parameters: I need a little more time.

\N<Hebeta>Big sister... your breathing is very rough. The Mind Lyuda
is corroding your body, isn't it?

\N<Segi>Ah, perhaps that's the case... But... But what I must do
is...

\N<Hebeta>I understand. You're not the type to throw in the towel.
That's why... you know what you should do for that reason,
right?

\N<Segi>Haah... Haah... Again, you're saying... to seek your help to
ease this pain...?

\N<Hebeta>...I have no intention of forcing you. It's an important
matter, so I think it should be entirely your own decision.

\N<Segi>What to do... it's already been decided. I should have made
up my mind during that time.

\N<Segi>I understand that it's not something to be easily dismissed
with simple words like 'once or twice'.

\N<Segi>But... even so, I think this is necessary. Yes, just like an
essential rite of passage.
\N<Segi>So... it's okay. My purpose hasn't wavered.

\N<Hebeta>...What will you do? You still have feelings of guilt
towards your husband, don't you?

\N<Hebeta>Understood. I will simply follow your decision to the end.
And... it may be tough, but I think it's the right choice.

\N<Hebeta>You're anxious, right? But don't worry, I understand. I'm
properly blindfolded.

\N<Hebeta>So, does this make you feel a bit more at ease? Don't worry,
I can't see your body from here.

\N<Hebeta>...So you just need to relax and leave everything to me.
Pretend I'm not even here; it's just you alone.

In this unusual situation of exposing her genitals in front
of a man who is not her beloved, the reassurance that her
body is not being seen provides Segi with some relief.

\N<Hebeta>Right now, you're just focusing your mind before an
important match begins. It might only be a small comfort...
but how about it? Can you think of it that way?

\N<Segi>To be honest... it's, of course, difficult... but... if it's
necessary... then, a little...

\N<Hebeta>Yeah, that's fine. It will all be over while you're doing
that. I'll finish everything while you're thinking of
something else.

The young man who calls himself Hebeta seems to be telling
the truth. However... even knowing that, her body reacts
sensitively.

But that was to be expected. Even if her mind understands,
it's not so easy to separate mind and body without struggle.

\N<Segi>(This is... necessary for the battle that's about to begin.
Nnn... Ah, even though my mind understands that... Ah, ah...
my heart is rejecting it... and confused.)

\N<Segi>(Even if... this act is an essential measure for the
upcoming battle... is this really the right thing to do?)
\N<Hebeta>...How about it? Are you feeling a bit better now...?
\N<Hebeta>That's good then. Relax, it's almost over?
\N<Hebeta>It'll be over soon. That's why I want you to bear with it.

That's right... No matter how much my heart is confused, my
body is indeed becoming somewhat relieved. That's a fact.

There's no way I can fight in such a state... So this is
necessary for the sake of our objective.
I'm not faltering. I'm just... using this person...

\N<Hebeta>It seems like you were lost in thought. How about it, did it
distract you a little?

\N<Hebeta>Sorry... Even though I said there's no other intention, this
must still be embarrassing for you, right...?

After a moment of silence, Hebeta apologized to Segi. No
matter the purpose that must be fulfilled, it's impossible
not to feel shame.

\N<Segi>I... won't deny it. No matter how much I resist... yes,
indeed, the heart and body are... Nn... con... connected...

\N<Hebeta>You're right. I must not have been considerate enough. I'll
reflect on that.

\N<Hebeta>No, let me reflect? I wasn't thinking about you. By the next
time... I'll think of a better way.

\N<Hebeta>Yeah... After properly considering your situation... I'll
find a way to make your body feel at ease...
I need a little more time.
\N<Segi>Haa... haa... The effects of Mind Lyuda on my body...

\N<Segi>Th-that's something... I've been aware of for a long time.
But that doesn't mean... it's the same as running away from
here...
\N<Segi>I have to do it... I have to be the one to do it...
